quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  19,83,Seest thou not that we send the Satans against the Infidels to urge them into sin
  19,84,Wherefore be not thou in haste with them; for a small number of days do we number to them
  19,85,One day we will gather the God-fearing before the God of Mercy with honours due
  19,86,"But the sinners will we drive unto Hell, like flocks driven to the watering"
  19,87,"None shall have power to intercede, save he who hath received permission at the hands of the God of Mercy"
  19,88,"They say: \"The God of Mercy hath gotten offspring"
  19,89,Now have ye done a monstrous thing
  19,90,"Almost might the very Heavens be rent thereat, and the Earth cleave asunder, and the mountains fall down in fragments"
  19,91,That they ascribe a son to the God of Mercy
  19,92,when it beseemeth not the God of Mercy to beget a son
  19,93,Verily there is none in the Heavens and in the Earth but shall approach the God of Mercy as a servant
  19,94,"He hath taken note of them, and numbered them with exact numbering"
  19,95,"And each of them shall come to Him, on the day of Resurrection, singly"
  19,96,But love will the God of Mercy vouchsafe to those who believe and do the things that be right
  19,97,"Verily we have made this Koran easy and in thine own tongue, that thou mayest announce glad tidings by it to the God-fearing, and that thou mayest warn the contentious by it"
  19,98,How many generations have we destroyed before them! Canst thou search out one of them? or canst thou hear a whisper from them